   "exercise_v2": [
      {
         "question": "Is new knowledge built upon previous knowledge?",
         "yesNoAnswer": "Yes",
         "additionalInfo": "Learning is a process of association that becomes more efficient when new knowledge is built upon prior knowledge. For this reason, children play a central role in their own learning process, as they continuously connect new information with what they already know."
      },
      {
         "question": "Is there a relationship between texts and a numerical axis (like a road)?",
         "yesNoAnswer": "Yes",
         "additionalInfo": "This analogy is valid because, when reading a word, we follow a clear direction: from the first letter to the last. However, it is important to remember that numbers do not have a defined 'final' point, as previously discussed in the <i>First Steps</i> section."
      }
